	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings people,<br><br>i am about to start a monk but please let me tell you why i decided that ! Please read the following :<br><br>i am playing a 18 lvl paladin named Fenamdar on the Quellious server. I like the lyfestyle of a good char and the benefits (and hardships) that it brings. However...i decided to go to LOIO for exp...nice place for my lvl.<br><br>Anyway in order to scout around i started an Iksar monk in order to go (and run as fast as i could) in LOIO and scout around the sights and then know at least the scenery before i ventured there with the pally. Then i would delete the Iksar since i was only testing...BUT...hehehe...i liked Cabilis, i liked the Guild...and decided to keep him. EVEN AT LVL 1 ITS VERY FUN ! <br><br>But since he is only lvl 1...i can easily delete him and make one with putting the bonus points in the right attributes ! HOWEVER:<br><br>I read 2 guides... The FIRST said to put everything on agi (but they start with 100).<br><br>The other guide...the SECOND one said to put them all on his 75 starting strength. <br><br>That is why i am confused ! TWO COMPLETELY DIFFERENT guides.<br><br>I appreciate all your input and help i can get. <br><br>The only thing i need is info on where to put the starting bonus points...for IKSAR...NOT FOR HUMAN.<br><br>Thank you.<br><br>Fenamdar<br>Legion of Velious<br>Quellious<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
