	   <tr><td colspan=2>I third that opinion.&nbsp;&nbsp;If I were to start over again, STR would be numero uno followed by STA.  I can't remember exactly what I did but I think I put a lot of points into AGI.  Oh well.<br><br>QUOTE:<br>STR-equipment is abundant.<br><br>Very true, and relatively cheap at least for the low-mid level stuff (Orc Fang Earrings, Jagged Bands), but IMO my STR is still WAAAAAY low (103 ATM) and I would be happy to have as much stinking STR (damage-inflicting capability) gear as possible.<br><br>One last point, with the addition of Wu's armor plus the naturally high AGI of Iksars, I would say there is absolutely no reason to add to AGI when starting out.  All of the Wu's gear has AGI bonuses, and fairly nice ones at that.<br><br>Alright I've rambled enough.  Good luck with the new lizard.<br><br>Zasshatiz Ezzekkiel<br>--34 Iksar Monk--<br>&lt;Dark Reformation&gt;<br>-Luclin Server-<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
